25|$|Mathematically, {{applying}} a Gaussian blur to an image {{is the same}} as convolving the image with a <b>Gaussian</b> <b>function.</b> This is also known as a two-dimensional Weierstrass transform. By contrast, convolving by a circle (i.e., a circular box blur) would more accurately reproduce the bokeh effect. Since the Fourier transform of a Gaussian is another Gaussian, {{applying a}} Gaussian blur has the effect of reducing the image's high-frequency components; a Gaussian blur is thus a low pass filter.|$|E
